description:
This is NGC6164 emission nebular in the constellation of Norma, captured from the Michael Jones Observatory in September 2019.  The nebular has formed from the intense radiation of the central O Type star. The nebula is enveloped by a delicate blue shroud that is thought to have formed from an earlier active phase of the O star.

This image is a product combining hydrogen-alpha filtered images with Oxygen III filtered images to produce a bi-colour image.

System details
Telescope: AG Optical Systems 0.3 meter iDK,
Focal length 2121 mm
Camera: mono FLI ML16200 with a Loadstar X2 on an Astrodon MOAG off-axis guider.
Adaptive Optics: SXV-AO-LF
Observatory: Scopedome 3m
Acquisition software: Voyager
Plate size: 44' x 35'
Hydrgen-alpha filter 25 x 20 minutes
Oyxgen III filter 66 x 20 minutes
title: NGC6164 nebula
